subject: p14727722
Findings: Interval placement of endotracheal tube terminating 46 cm above the carina, and a nasogastric tube terminating in the stomach. Right internal jugular central venous catheter terminates in the proximal superior vena cava, with no visible pneumothorax. Stable cardiomegaly accompanied by mild pulmonary vascular congestion. Questionable small left pleural effusion.
